text.__SUMMARY__: Corymbia hylandii, commonly known as Hyland's bloodwood, is a bloodwood native to QueenslandThe tree typically grows to a height of 10 metres (33 ft) and has persistent grey-brown or red-brown bark on the trunk and larger branches. Adult leaves are disjunct with a narrow lanceolate to lanceolate shape, glossy green in color, 10 to 18 centimetres (3.9 to 7.1 in) long and 7 to 20 mm (0.28 to 0.79 in) wide.
